      <Docs>
        <summary>
            The flag that enables or disables a capability to have UltraSSD Enabled
            Virtual Machines on Dedicated Hosts of the Dedicated Host Group. For
            the Virtual Machines to be UltraSSD Enabled, UltraSSDEnabled flag for
            the resource needs to be set true as well. The value is defaulted to
            'false' when not provided. Please refer to
            https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-machines/disks-enable-ultra-ssd
            for more details on Ultra SSD feature. **Note:** The ultraSSDEnabled
            setting can only be enabled for Host Groups that are created as zonal.
            Minimum api-version: 2022-03-01.
            </summary>
